        <h2>üöÄ Setup Guide</h2>
        
        <div class="setup-section">
            <h3>üìã Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Flutter SDK 3.x or later installed</li>
                <li>Android Studio with Android SDK (for Android builds)</li>
                <li>Xcode (for iOS builds, macOS only)</li>
                <li>Node.js 18+ (for Supabase Edge Functions)</li>
                <li>Supabase account</li>
                <li>Firebase account</li>
                <li>API Keys: Gemini AI, OpenWeather, NewsAPI</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="setup-section">
            <h3>1Ô∏è‚É£ Clone or Download Flutter Source</h3>
            <p>The complete Flutter source code is available in the <code>/life_management_app</code> directory.</p>
            <pre><code>cd life_management_app</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <div class="setup-section">
            <h3>2Ô∏è‚É£ Install Flutter Dependencies</h3>
            <pre><code>flutter pub get</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <div class="setup-section">
            <h3>3Ô∏è‚É£ Set Up Supabase Backend</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Create a new Supabase project at <a href="https://supabase.com">supabase.com</a></li>
                <li>Copy your project URL and anon key</li>
                <li>Run the database schema:
                    <pre><code>psql -h your-db-host -U postgres -d your-database -f supabase/schema.sql</code></pre>
                </li>
                <li>Deploy Edge Functions:
                    <pre><code>cd supabase/functions
supabase functions deploy crypto-prices
supabase functions deploy gemini-assistant</code></pre>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        
        <div class="setup-section">
            <h3>4Ô∏è‚É£ Set Up Firebase</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Create a Firebase project</li>
                <li>Add Android and iOS apps to your Firebase project</li>
                <li>Download <code>google-services.json</code> (Android) and <code>GoogleService-Info.plist</code> (iOS)</li>
                <li>Place files in:
                    <ul>
                        <li><code>android/app/google-services.json</code></li>
                        <li><code>ios/Runner/GoogleService-Info.plist</code></li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Enable Firebase Cloud Messaging</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        
        <div class="setup-section">
            <h3>5Ô∏è‚É£ Configure Environment Variables</h3>
            <p>Create a <code>.env</code> file or use Flutter compile-time variables:</p>
            <pre><code># Build with environment variables
flutter build apk --dart-define=SUPABASE_URL=your_url \
  --dart-define=SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_key \
  --dart-define=GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_key \
  --dart-define=OPENWEATHER_API_KEY=your_weather_key \
  --dart-define=NEWS_API_KEY=your_news_key</code></pre>
            
            <p>Or update <code>lib/core/config/env_config.dart</code> with your keys (not recommended for production).</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="setup-section">
            <h3>6Ô∏è‚É£ Run the Application</h3>
            <h4>Mobile (Android/iOS)</h4>
            <pre><code>flutter run</code></pre>
            
            <h4>Web</h4>
            <pre><code>flutter run -d chrome</code></pre>
        </div>
        
